The paper discusses a framework for answering complex questions using a combination of search engines, reading comprehension models, and semantic parsers. This suggests that the paper could fall under several sub-categories of computer science, including natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), and neural networks (cs.NE). Among these, cs.CL and cs.AI are the most likely categories, as they directly relate to the paper's focus on language understanding and reasoning.
